  "texts": [
    "Figure 2 shows the annual publication trends from 2000 to 2024, retrieved using the queries \"Artificial Intelligence + Olfaction\" and \"Artificial Intelligence + Gustation.\"",
    "Research in AI-driven olfaction began earlier and showed a significant rise after 2010, aligning with the broader adoption of machine learning technologies.",
    "In contrast, gustatory applications of AI started gaining traction after 2004, with a sharp increase post-2020.",
    "This growth reflects a rising interdisciplinary interest in sensory science and highlights how AI methodologies are increasingly applied to decode and optimize flavor perception across both smell and taste domains.",
    "To ensure transparency and methodological rigor in capturing the research landscape, we adopted a structured search and filtering process based on PRISMA guidelines."
